Good news, I have a workaround !

@Luap99 the rootless-netns shell made me realize that it was not able to access $HOME in it. This is because that user has an "exotic" home in `/var/lib/deploy` . Creating a `seb` user with defaults worked well. 

Not sure if there is a fix to have in podman like add a warning. Maybe a simple note in the doc saying "home directory should / should not be X" ?
